# OMBI ŌĆö Open Metaverse Browser Initiative

> **This file is the project's shared knowledge base.** Any developer or AI assistant who clones this repository inherits this file as their starting context. It is not a sequential log ŌĆö it does not record session history or append dated entries. It describes what the project *is right now*: architecture, codebase structure, dependencies, build decisions and their rationale, conventions, and roadmap status. Update sections in place as the project evolves. Session-level notes belong in session log files, not here.

## Overview

**OMBI** (Open Metaverse Browser Initiative) is an organizational unit under the Metaverse Standards Forum. Its mission is to define and build a reference implementation of the Open Metaverse Browser (OMB).

The project produces two components:

- **Sneeze** ŌĆö the Metaverse Browser Engine (MBE). A standalone, reusable engine library (static `.lib`). Analogous to Blink in the web browser world. All code lives in namespace `SNEEZE`. Owns all third-party dependencies (Wasmtime, SPIRV-Tools, OpenXR, curl, RmlUi, ANARI, nlohmann/json, Filament, Halogen, BoringSSL, jwt-cpp) and the engine modules that wrap them (`sneeze/` core + `sneeze/control/`, `context/` + `context/scene/` + `context/console/` + `context/network/` + `context/storage/` + `context/msf/`, `viewport/renderer/` + `viewport/view/`, `deps/wasm/` + `deps/spirv/` + `deps/xr/` + `deps/ui/` + `deps/compute/` + `deps/stb/`, `persona/`, and future `smap/`, `identity/`, `audio/`). Public API headers live in `include/` (consumed by Artemis); private implementation headers live in `src/`. All test suites are compiled into a single `SneezeTest` executable (run all with no args, or select suites with `--wasm`, `--spv`, `--xr`, `--ui`, `--compute`, `--vox`, `--jws`, `--network`, `--storage`). Another team could build a different metaverse browser on top of Sneeze without touching Artemis.

- **Artemis** ŌĆö the metaverse browser application. The single `.exe`. Analogous to Chrome/Chromium. A thin application layer that consumes Sneeze: window management (`canvas/`), user chrome, and `main()`. Owns SDL3 (windowing/input is application-level, not engine-level). Artemis is **not open source** ŌĆö proprietary copyright headers.

Sneeze is a static `.lib`; Artemis is a separate repo (sibling directory) that compiles Sneeze inline via `add_subdirectory`. All namespaces, include guards, string literals, and source references use `SNEEZE`.

**Dependency ownership:** Sneeze declares and owns all third-party engine dependencies. Artemis depends on Sneeze and SDL3. When Artemis links against Sneeze, CMake transitively pulls in all of Sneeze's dependencies via PUBLIC declarations. SDL3 belongs to Artemis, not Sneeze ŌĆö the engine is embeddable without owning windowing.

