pp`. |
| `CONTAINER` | `context` | Runtime manifestation of an MSF file ŌĆö wraps WASM modules, SPIR-V shaders, storage silos, SOM objects, and map data. Top-level class in `SNEEZE` namespace (defined in `include/Container.h`). Contains nested CID class + `eTRUST` enum. pImpl pattern. Constructor takes `CONTEXT*` + `const CID*` (copies CID by value into Impl). `Open(FABRIC*)` increments refcount; on 0->1 transition creates CONSOLE::STREAM via `m_pContext->Console()->Stream_Open(&m_CID)`, STORAGE::SILO via `m_pContext->Storage()->Silo_Open(&m_CID)` (+ Attach), and DEP::WASM_STORE via `m_pContext->WasmRuntime()->Store_Open()` (+ SetHostData to `m_pContext` + InitializeLinker with 32 host functions). `Close(FABRIC*)` decrements; on 1->0 transition tears down in reverse: WasmRuntime()->Store_Close, Silo Detach + Silo_Close, Stream_Close. `m_apFabric` is `vector<FABRIC*>` tracking which fabrics hold this container open. Containers persist in `CONTEXT::Impl::m_umpContainer` at refcount 0 as lightweight identity shells ŌĆö not deleted until CONTEXT destruction. `Identity()` returns `const CID*` (pointer to the Impl's authoritative CID ŌĆö pointer identity matters, multiple consumers must compare pointers not values). `Key()` returns `const std::string&` (pre-computed map key). `~Impl()` logs via `Engine()->Log()` if destroyed with nonzero refcount, deletes all owned MAP_OBJECTs from `m_apMap_Object`. **Scene Node Handle Table:** CONTAINER owns the authoritative handle-to-NODE mapping for all nodes created by its WASM modules. Two handle maps: `m_umpNode` (`unordered_map<uint64_t, NODE*>`, keyed by `twObjectIx`) and `m_umpFabric` (`unordered_map<uint64_t, FABRIC*>`, keyed by `twFabricIx`). Monotonic counters `m_twObjectIx_Next` and `m_twFabricIx_Next` for auto-assignment. **Critical design decision:** `m_umpNode` is an `unordered_map`, NOT a `vector` ŌĆö object indices are 48-bit values (range 1 to 2^48-4) and may be sparse. A `vector` would attempt to allocate physical memory for all entries between 0 and the max index. Constants: `OBJECTIX_NULL` (0), `OBJECTIX_IDENTITY` (0xFFFFFFFFFFFF ŌĆö auto-assign sentinel), `OBJECTIX_MAX` (0xFFFFFFFFFFFB), `OBJECTIX_ERROR` (0xFFFFFFFFFFFC). `FABRICIX_*` parallels. Public API: `Node_Root(twFabricIx, pRMCObject)` ŌĆö creates root node for a fabric (guards: `pRMCObject != null`, fabric exists, no existing root). `Node_Open(twParentIx, pRMCObject)` ŌĆö creates child node (guards: parent exists in handle table). `Node_Close(twObjectIx)` ŌĆö removes node from handle table, deletes NODE + MAP_OBJECT. `Node_Find(twObjectIx)` ŌĆö lookup by handle. `Instance_Open(twFabricIx, sUrl, sHash, aWasmBytes)` ŌĆö compiles + instantiates WASM module. `Instance_Close(twFabricIx, sUrl, sHash)` ŌĆö tears down instance. Mutex: `m_mxContainer` (recursive_mutex) guards all public entry points (`Node_Root`, `Node_Open`, `Node_Close`). `Node_Create` is internal-only (called inside the lock). `Node_Create` constructs a `MAP_OBJECT_CELESTIAL`, copies RMCOBJECT wire-format fields (name as wide-to-narrow char conversion, celestial type, position, scale, bound, radius, mass, orbit), creates NODE, calls Initialize, stores in both `m_umpNode` and `m_apMap_Object`. RMCOBJECT is a 432-byte packed C struct (`#pragma pack(push, 1)`, `static_assert(sizeof == 432)`) defined in `src/context/scene/MapObject.h` ŌĆö the wire format for WASM-to-C++ scene object transfer. Contains sub-structs: OBJECT_HEAD (with TWORD Self containing 48-bit ObjectIx), RMCOBJECT_NAME (48 wchar_t), RMCOBJECT_TYPE, RMCOBJECT_OWNER, RMCOBJECT_RESOURCE, RMCOBJECT_TRANSFORM, RMCOBJECT_ORBIT, RMCOBJECT_BOUND, RMCOBJECT_PROPERTIES. TWORD is a 6-byte packed struct with `ObjectIx()` accessor that masks the top 2 bytes. Impl members: `m_pContainer`, `m_pContext`, `m_CID` (by value), `m_sKey`, `m_nCount_Open`, `m_mxContainer` (recursive_mutex), `m_pStream` (CONSOLE::STREAM*), `m_pSilo` (STORAGE::SILO*), `m_pWasm_Store` (DEP::WASM_STORE*), `m_twObjectIx_Next`, `m_umpNode` (unordered_map<uint64_t, NODE*>), `m_apMap_Object` (vector<MAP_OBJECT*>), `m_twFabricIx_Next`, `m_umpFabric` (unordered_map<uint64_t, FABRIC*>). |
